			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	We are currently seeking a highly movtivated Sales Representative&nbsp; based in our Bethesda, MD office.&nbsp; This sales role is responsible for managing and developing a geographic territory of accounts in the Non-Profit sector, including Education, Healthcare, Arts and Culture and Community services.</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Key Job Responsibilities:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Follow up on inbound leads received from marketing programs; webinars, trade shows, etc.</li>
	<li>
		Research target companies in the non-profit sector to understand their key business priorities and translate how WealthEngine solutions can help meet their goals</li>
	<li>
		Proactively find additional new business opportunities through initiative and creativity, as well as working closely with sales management to develop and maintain target lists of prospects; this includes cold calling and prospecting through email</li>
	<li>
		Conduct full sales cycle process from qualifying leads to close of the sale</li>
	<li>
		Properly maintain a pipeline of business - new opportunities and renewals via Salesforce.com - documenting discussions, emails, proposals, client feedback. etc.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Qualifications:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Bachelor&#39;s degree in Business, Marketing or other relevant area of study preferred</li>
	<li>
		1-3 years experience working in sales, &nbsp;meeting and surpassing targets</li>
	<li>
		Experience working with in a non-profit or service sector is desirable</li>
	<li>
		Proven ability to creatively identify new accounts and opportunities</li>
	<li>
		Experience and ability to manage existing accounts and identify up-sell opportunities; ability to work with a sales quota on a monthly/quarterly/annual basis</li>
</ul>
<p>
	WealthEngine, Inc. is a rapidly growing, venture backed technology company with a strong reputation as the leading provider of wealth identification and prospect research solutions.&nbsp; Our solutions help our clients identify and target prospective donors and customers with its proprietary analytics and rating system.</p>
<p>
	We offer a competitive salary and comprehensive employee benefits including medical, dental, vision insurance, 401K plan and a &quot;Healthly Lifestyle&quot; allowance.&nbsp; Send resume to <a href="mailto:careers@wealthengine.com">careers@wealthengine.com</a></p>
